<br>
Her one worry was Silenae. She knew exactly how she would look at this, all family were equal. They had gone through this with the male enchanter, Jeronic years past. Of course Vanti would not be punished by any but her. <br>
<br>
Stiffling a sigh, she made eye contact with Vanti and gave him a small smile. She knew how hard it was for him. But knew too he would be happy with the family. Furrowing her brow, do knights of Innoruuk feel happiness? <br>
<br>
Turning to her family, she bowed, then moving twards Kerridwynn and Demaste she kneeled. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;He is under my care, for a blood debt. His place in these halls, will be left up to the rest of you as I am biased.&quot;<br>
<br>
